<div id="head">
  <h1>Internet Access at Hotels</h1>
</div>
<div class="content">
<p>It's difficult to find out whether a hotel has Internet access without actually staying there. They rarely knows what you mean. Web pages often claim they have "in-room Internet" when all they have is a phone jack. So this is  a list of hotels with information about available Internet access. Please <a href="mailto:nethotel@aaronsw.com">send me corrections and additions</a>.</p>
<p>
<a href="http://www.mercerhotel.com/">Mercer Hotel</a>: Dial-up, wireless coming soon. (2002-08-27, front desk)<br />
<a href="http://www.charleshotel.com/">Charles Hotel</a>: STSN T1. (2002-01-01, <a href="http://www.preferredhotels.com/values/hotel_descr.asp?membercode=BOSCH">preferred hotels</a>, Aaron Swartz)</p>

<p>Often hotel internet access is referred to as "high-speed Internet" or "broadband Internet". Asking whether the hotel has a "T1" is not effective since many hotels have a voice, not data T1 line.</p>

</div>
